{"title":"C-Bear emerges with 2nd generation DUB bottom brackets, eliminating SRAM spacer table","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/15/c-bear-emerges-with-2nd-generation-dub-bottom-brackets-eliminating-sram-spacer-table/","date":1631724813000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"799\" height=\"537\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14123121/C-Bear-DUB-BB-full-e1631724785536.jpeg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"C-Bear DUB BB full\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271550\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>C-Bear emerges with 2nd generation DUB bottom brackets that take up all the space, keeping those spacers in hibernation. C-Bear is known for its super smooth ceramic bottom brackets, pulley wheel, spanning manufactures and configurations.</p><div id=\"attachment_271554\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727.jpeg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271554\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727.jpeg\" alt=\"C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant\" width=\"963\" height=\"928\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727.jpeg 963w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-297x286.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-800x771.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-120x116.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-768x740.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 963px) 100vw, 963px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727.jpeg 963w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-297x286.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-800x771.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-120x116.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14121822/C-bear-dub-pf86-2gen-giant-e1631636556727-768x740.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271554\">c. C-Bear</p></div><p>When it comes to DUB bottom brackets, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/08/18/c-bear-solves-bb30-woes-new-pressfit-bottom-bracket-system/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">some configurations pop in easily</a> (with the correct tools), and some need spacers and a bit of troubleshooting for silky smooth perfection. That all changes with the newest iteration (2nd gen) of C-Bears BSA DUB, DUB BB30, PF30, and PF86.5 DUB bottom brackets.</p><p>The only change to the SRAM setup is eliminating the dreaded SRAM DUB spacer table and the spacer trial and error leaving only a SRAM pre-loading ring. The pre-loading ring still works just like the SRAM preload on the DUB cranksets with their own bottom brackets.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1340\" height=\"920\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart.jpg 1340w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-297x204.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-800x549.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-120x82.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-768x527.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-696x478.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-1068x733.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-612x420.jpg 612w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-100x70.jpg 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart.jpg 1340w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-297x204.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-800x549.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-120x82.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-768x527.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-696x478.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-1068x733.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-612x420.jpg 612w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/c-bear-bottom-bracket-chart-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><h2>Updated C-Bear Models</h2><ul><li>C-BEAR BSA DUB</li><li>C-BEAR PF86.5 DUB</li><li>C-BEAR DUB BB30</li><li>C-BEAR DUB PF30</li></ul><p>To find out that C-Bear bottom bracket you need, check out their <a href=\"https://www.c-bear.com/en/c-bear\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">BB finding tool HERE.</a></p><h2>Pricing and availably</h2><p>The new SRAM DUB bottom brackets from C-Bear are available now on the <a href=\"https://www.c-bear.com/en/products/sram-dub\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">C-Bear website</a>. Prices range from $160-$200 depending on the bearing options and configurations.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/C-Bear-Integrated-Sleeve-ceramic-bottom-brackets_all-internal-routing-compatible.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/C-Bear-Integrated-Sleeve-ceramic-bottom-brackets_all-internal-routing-compatible.jpg\" alt=\"C-Bear Integrated Sleeve ceramic bottom bracket, all internal routing compatible BBs\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1050\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/C-Bear-Integrated-Sleeve-ceramic-bottom-brackets_all-internal-routing-compatible.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/C-Bear-Integrated-Sleeve-ceramic-bottom-brackets_all-i